name: Jayveersinh Raj
headline: Data Scientist/ML and AI engineer
creator: False
bio:
🚀 Passionate ML and DL Professional | Natural Language Enthusiast | Full Stack Data Scientist 📊

Welcome to my world of data-driven innovation! As a dynamic professional deeply immersed in the realms of Machine Learning (ML) and Deep Learning (DL), with a particular fondness for Natural Language Processing (NLP), I'm on a relentless quest to push the boundaries of what's possible with data.

👨‍💻 With a robust skill set and hands-on experience as a Full Stack Data Scientist, I navigate seamlessly from conceptualizing cutting-edge algorithms to deploying scalable solutions, impacting industries far and wide.

🔍 Curiosity fuels my journey as I continually delve into the intricate nuances of language, leveraging large-scale language models and AI agents to unravel new possibilities in every project.

💡 From spearheading industrial endeavors to collaborating on transformative ventures, my GitHub repository is a testament to my commitment to innovation. (Check it out: github.com/Javeersinh-Raj)

🌐 Data Science isn't just a profession; it's a revolution reshaping the landscape of every sector. I'm fervently driven to explore diverse domains, seeking opportunities to make a tangible impact through the power of language models.

📧 Let's connect and ignite transformative conversations: jayveersinhraj53@gmail.com 🤓😄

name: Vitalii Volobuev
headline: Head Of Research at Lab of Applied Neuroscience
creator: False
bio:
Vitaliy Volobuev is head of Lab of Neuroscience and Neurotechnologies.  Vitaly received his Bachelor degree at Innopolis University, his major is in Data Science. During his free time, Vitaly had proposed to open a branch for research in neuroscience and in 2016 has taken a supervising position of the lab of Neuroscience and Neurotechnologies with focus on Brain-Machine Interfaces. Has participated in developing brain-controlled robots (2019) and ``Kamaz'' truck drivers attention monitoring system (2018). Vitaly also works in Calejo AI as Senior full-stack Data Scientist and lead mathematician at AI in Construction branch of Diginavis. His work there mainly addresses the differential geometry analysis and machine learning models' development. Vitaly's research interest is in Computational Neuroscience, raw EEG analysis and functional connectivity.

Scientific activity achievements available here:
Researchgate profile https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Vitaly_Volobuev2
Publons profile https://publons.com/researcher/3954818/vitaliy-volobuev/

headline: Rust Software Engineer | AI & AGI Enthusiast | Tech-Frontiersman
creator: False
bio: Driven Software Engineer with a strong foundation in Rust and a rich history in blockchain development, including work on Substrate for a Polkadot network parachain. name: Igor Belov
headline: iOS developer and computer science enthusiast
creator: False
bio:
As an experienced iOS software developer, I possess a wide range of skills and expertise in the field.

I have had the opportunity to work with many different frameworks, however, I believe that responsibly, as well as the ability to understand and solve problems, is much more important than knowing some tool.

My strong foundation in Computer Science allows me to understand the underlying systems and design efficient solutions. I also have experience with DevOps tasks such as setting up CI/CD pipelines to optimize deployment processes and improve the overall software development life cycle. Furthermore, I enjoy mentoring and leading other team members, I am always willing to share my knowledge and experience, and to collaborate with others to help achieve common goals.

I am a firm believer in the importance of writing clean and organized code, although it's not always possible to achieve it, especially while dealing with legacy code.

And actually, I speak in Swift.

name: Bogdan Fedotov
location: St Petersburg, St Petersburg City, Russia
headline: Gameplay Programmer (Unity, Unreal) and Game Engine Programmer
creator: False
bio:
( •̀ ω •́ )✧ 3+ years Unity Android/iOS game development experience.
(≧∀≦)ゞ  1+ year Unity experience of porting mobile games to WebGL
Proficient with Unity asset optimization techniques, Unity Addressables, LeoECS, and more. 
Have experience writing Unity packages, editor extensions, and ShaderLab shaders. 

-- Game Engine programming experience --
+ Currently developing a LevEngine game engine in a small team, available at https://github.com/mrLegenius/LevEngine
+ Implemented a simple graphics engine with DirectX 11 and C++, available at https://github.com/Fenrir7Asteron/ComputerGraphicsLabs

-- Unreal Engine experience --
Have two game vertical slices developed in UE5 available on itch.io:

1. Foodborne is a Top Down Shooter. Developed this project in a team of 4 people. I took multiple roles in this team: Lead Game Designer, Gameplay C++ Programmer, and Sound Designer. I implemented part of game mechanics in Foodborne with C++ and created dynamic SFX with Meta Sounds. 
We demonstrated the vertical slice of our game on Playsar Fest 2023. Both judges and players warmly received the project.

2. Light Eater is a 3D Beat 'em Up with classical 2.5D gameplay inspired by Streets of Rage. I implemented everything in this project with Blueprints.

Eager to study something new: be it programming stuff, game/sound design, or human languages.
